BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:DBwde3atHE51x1cIN8vZS
SUMMARY:Blood Drive: Bloodworks Northwest
DTSTAMP:20260413T004137Z
DTSTART:20260417T101500Z
DESCRIPTION:Phinney Center\\\, Blue Building – Room 6 \\nDonate blood to he
	lp local transplant patients. \\nBlood donors play a critical role in supp
	orting local transplant patients. Over 49\\\,000 transplants were performe
	d in the U.S. last year. An organ transplant may need up to 40 red cell un
	its\\\, 30 platelet units\\\, and 25 plasma units. As a blood donor\\\, yo
	u make organ transplantation possible and provide patients with another re
	newed chance at a healthy life. Donating blood takes about an hour and is 
	urgently needed. Book an appointment to give blood today and give hope to 
	our community. \\nAppointments are available between 10:15 AM to 4:15 PM. 
	Sign up for your appointment by clicking here. \\nAppointments are require
	d for the best possible donation experience.\\nPhoto ID required.\\nFor sa
	fety\\\, we kindly request no visitors under 16 at our donation sites.\\nE
	at a hearty meal and drink plenty of fluids prior to donation.\n\nhttps://
	www.phinneycenter.org/event/blood-drive-bloodworks-northwest-5/\n\nFrom Ph
	inney Neighborhood Association (PNA)
URL:https://www.phinneycenter.org/event/blood-drive-bloodworks-northwest-5/
LOCATION:Phinney Center Campus: Blue (upper) Building\\\, 6532 Phinney Ave.
	 N.\\\, Seattle\\\, WA\\\, 98103\\\, United States
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:phinney-neighborhood-association
CATEGORIES:Phinney Neighborhood Association (PNA)
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT6H
